The list of activities used in this process are the following. Please only use these activities to generate constraints:
O_Create Offer, A_Pending, A_Cancelled, A_Complete, A_Validating, A_Submitted, A_Incomplete, A_Denied, O_Sent (mail and online), A_Accepted, O_Accepted, O_Sent (online only)

Creating an offer is a mandatory step in the loan application process. Submitting an application cannot occur multiple times. We may have a maximum of one application pending event. One application can have only one of the outcomes: pending or cancelled. An application can either be cancelled or denied. There are two possible sending procedures for offers: 1) mail and online 2) only online. When an application is cancelled, no more offer should be created for this application. Acceptance of an application never occurs after the completion of the application. All pending applications must be preceded by an accepted offer. Any application incomplete event must be proceeded by the validation of the application.

